block vars
  - var activeLink = 'vue';
  - var title = 'List Button Vue Component | Framework7 Vue Documentation';

block content
  .docs-wrap
    .docs-nav
      include ../_docs-vue-menu
    .docs-content
      h1 List Button Vue Component
      p List Button Vue component represents Framework7's <a href="../docs/buttons.html#list-block-buttons">List Block Button</a> element. They are intended to be used inside of the <a href="list.html">List</a> component.
      h2 Usage examples
      h4 Minimal Layout
      pre
        code
          :code
            <f7-list>
              <f7-list-button>Button 1</f7-list-button>
              <f7-list-button>Button 2</f7-list-button>
            </f7-list>
      p Renders to:
      pre
        code
          :code
            <div class="list-block">
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <a href="#" class="item-link list-button">Button 1</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="#" class="item-link list-button">Button 2</a>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

      h4 Colored Buttons
      pre
        code
          :code
            <f7-list>
              <f7-list-button color="red">Red Button</f7-list-button>
              <f7-list-button color="green">Green Button</f7-list-button>
            </f7-list>
      h4 Control Buttons in Inset List
      pre
        code
          :code
            <f7-list inset>
              <f7-list-button open-panel="left">Open Panel</f7-list-button>
              <f7-list-button open-popup="#my-popup">Open Popup</f7-list-button>
            </f7-list>
